description: {"blocks":[{"key":"6lb8e","text":"Protocol for rat brain processing in order to perform histological analyses","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8eetd","text":"Deeply anesthetize animals with sodium pentobarbital (50 mg/kg, i.p.)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"drg98","text":"Perfuse through the left ventricle with saline [0.9% (wt/vol)] at room temperature (RT)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fv57e","text":"Perfuse again with ice-cold formaldehyde solution 4% in PBS buffered for histology","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ebarj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9r5l2","text":"Wash twice with 0.1 M PBS and process for paraffin embedding following standard procedures (performed by an external facility) or store brains in 0.1 M PBS at 4 °C, alternatively (not for over a month without changing the PBS)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4td14","text":"Remove brains and post-fix them for 24 h in the same fixative","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"38smo","text":"Cryoprotect for 24-48 h (until they sink) in 30% sucrose at 4 °C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"aana8","text":"Immerse brains 30 s in 2-methylbutane and store at -80 °C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8fcui","text":"Perform sectioning with a sliding microtome at 5-μm-thickness for paraffin samples or","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"82vqc","text":"in a cryostat at 20- or 30-μm-thickness for frozen samples. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
